<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPPERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WRIGHT TIME FOR PAY RAISE?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM DESERT, Calif. _ The Los Angeles Clipper who last week
promised to `hold down the fort' until top draft pick Michael
Olowokandi's return from Europe, now says he's prepared to abandon
his low post.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's time to go,'' third-year power forward Lorenzen Wright
said Friday after his agent, Robert Fayne, put the Clippers on
pay-me-or-trade-me alert.
</P>
<P>
   Wright _ who averaged nine points and 8.8 rebounds in the second
year of his three-year deal _ wants a six-year contract extension
adding up to Fayne's interpretation of fair-market value.
</P>
<P>
   According to a Clippers source, that number would begin with the
maximum stake of $9 million per season, under terms of the new
collective bargaining agreement, and total $60 million over the six
years. The Clippers aren't wild about those numbers or the
chronology.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is not the time,'' Elgin Baylor, the team's vice
president of basketball operations, said. ``It's the second day of
training camp. I don't think it's the appropriate time to get into
this.''
</P>
<P>
   The player and his agent think this should be the Wright time.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love all of the fans,'' said Wright, whose post-lockout
timing might not inspire much sympathy, ``but my family comes
first. In order to take care of my family, I have to have a
commitment.''
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers' league-structured commitment to the 6-foot-11
Wright is worth less than $2 million this season, and a spoken
desire to re-sign him _ for their interpretation of market value _
after his current contract expires.
</P>
<P>
   The third pick in the 1984 draft, Michael Jordan, never asked to
renegotiate what quickly became a less-than-market-value contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``We like Lorenzen,'' said Baylor, speaking for a franchise that
has until March 13 to offer an extension. ``We'd like to keep him
here. We feel he's an integral part of this team. At this point in
time, we have no intention of trading him.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-23-99 0206EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
