<P>
   &UR; AUTOS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-VOLVO (Undated) _ In recent weeks, Volvo has again
appeared on the corporate dinner table; Fiat S.p.A., the Ford Motor
Company and possibly others have been weighing a purchase of the
Swedish company's automotive division. The buzz has sent Volvo's
stock spiraling first up, then down. Enjoy the S80 while you can.
It may be one of the last products an independent Volvo produces.
By Dan Neil. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-BELTS (Undated) _ In Sweden more than 40 years ago,
automaker Volvo conducted its first test of a two-point safety
belt. It hired Nils Ivar Bohlin, now 75, a Swedish-born aircraft
engineer as the company's first safety engineer. He immediately
went to work on inventing a three-point safety belt, which was
installed as standard equipment in the 1959 Volvo. Since then,
Bohlin's invention has been used by automakers worldwide and is
credited with saving millions of lives. By Michelle Krebs. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
