these groups with something that is more important than assistance,
which is protection,'' de Mello said. ``Therefore the specter of
the well-fed dead _ those we feed but are unable to protect and
eventually are killed _ is something that we have been grappling
with for many years now.''
</P>
<P>
   The new world order is an environment without ideologies, which
however flawed may have at least provided symbols and ennobling
motivations in past conflicts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ideas are much smaller now,'' said Arthur Helton, an
international lawyer who directs migration projects at the Open
