<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
news stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Sunday, Jan. 24, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact David Brady at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   SENIOR-ROMANCE (Los Angeles) _ Whenever they're together, their
hands reach for each other. Their eyes flash when they talk about
their first meeting, 19 months ago. Imagine what this giddy couple,
Florence Alexander and Sam Rothman, will be like in another year or
so _ say, when he's 90 and she's 87. By Steve Carney. (Will move in
the ``n'' California and the ``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOARD-EDUCATION (Los Angeles) _ Tired of the squabbling that
can, at times, make them sound like an unhappy family, the men and
women who comprise the seven-member Los Angeles Board of Education
are about to undergo group therapy to foster cooperative skills. By
David R. Baker. (Will move in the ``n'' California and the ``a''
national news file.)
