</P>
<P>
   _ ``I received a resume and a note that said the recent high
school graduate wanted to earn $25 an hour _ `and not a nickel
less.' ''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``He had arranged for a pizza to be delivered to my office
during a lunch-hour interview. I asked him not to eat it until
later.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Said she had just graduated cum laude, but had no idea what
cum laude meant. However, she was proud of her grade point average.
It was 2.1.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Insisted on telling me that he wasn't afraid of hard work.
But insisted on adding that he was afraid of horses and didn't like
jazz, modern art or seafood.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The candidate never looked directly at me once during the
entire interview. Just stared at the floor.''
</P>
