   w/POPE _ Pope John Paul II comes to the Midwest as the American
Catholic Church and its 61 million members struggle harder than
ever to evangelize Generation Y and to hold on to young people who
have grown up in the church but drifted. Priest shortages are
rampant and the number choosing religious life dwindles. Crowds of
youth will come to see the pope, but dismiss his moral mandates. As
the aged pope nears the end of his papacy, the future of the church
lies in their hands. Will they accept church law which Jean Paul
has declared ``immutable'' on issues such as celibacy of priests,
birth control, abortion, homosexuality, and women in the pulpit? A
contrasting of their views with older Catholics. (Lyles, Dayton
Daily News). 30-35. MOVED FRIDAY
