<P>
   LEBANON-ISRAEL _ BEIRUT, Lebanon _ After 17 years of warfare,
people in the rolling hills and olive orchards in south Lebanon
wonder if they might finally again have peace _ a time when Israeli
troops might not occupy their land trade artillery with Lebanese
Hezbollah guerillas. For them, the war represents episodes like
last week's, when several civilians were killed by Israeli bombing
runs. For Israel, the war that many call ``Israel's Vietnam'' has
now outlasted the actual Vietnam War. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
