<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    99 invited to Masters
 &HT;    By Glenn Sheeley
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A field of 99 players invited for the 1999 Masters
April 8-11 will feature 14 first-time participants and four of the
world's top amateur players.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Kuchar, U.S. Amateur champion Hank Kuehne and British
Amateur champion Sergio Garcia of Spain are joined by U.S. Amateur
runner-up Tom McKnight.
</P>
<P>
   The first-time professionals will include Americans Brandel
Chamblee, Glen Day, Joe Durant, J.P. Hayes, Brandt Jobe, Frank
Lickliter and British Open runner-up Brian Watts.
</P>
<P>
   Mark O'Meara, who at 41 became the oldest player in history to
win two majors in the same year, is defending champion.
</P>
<P>
   Other Georgians in the field are Tommy Aaron, the 1973 Masters
champion; Billy Andrade and Stewart Cink; former Georgia Tech
player and 1998 PGA Tour leading moneywinner David Duval; Sea
Island's Davis Love III; and 1987 Masters champion Larry Mize of
Columbus.
</P>
<P>
   An expanded qualification process pushed Greg Norman into the
1999 field. For the first time the top 50 players in the Official
World Golf Rankings are invited if not otherwise eligible. Four
weeks prior to the Masters any new members of the top 50 also will
gain eligibility.
</P>
<P>
   Six-time champion Jack Nicklaus will miss for the first time in
40 years, recovering from hip replacement surgery scheduled for
Jan. 27.
</P>
<P>
   THE FIELD
</P>
<P>
   (including honorary, non-competing players)
</P>
<P>
   Tommy Aaron, Billy Andrade, Stuart Appleby, George Archer, Paul
Azinger, Severiano Ballesteros; Thomas Bjorn, Gay Brewer Jr.; Mark
Brooks, Olin Browne; Jack Burke Jr.; Mark Calcavecchia, Billy
Casper, Brandel Chamblee, Stewart Cink, Darren Clarke; Charles
Coody, John Cook, Fred Couples, Ben Crenshaw, John Daly, Glen Day,
Trevor Dodds, Joe Durant, David Duval, Steve Elkington, Ernie Els,
Bob Estes; Nick Faldo, Brad Faxon, Raymond Floyd, Doug Ford, Carlos
Franco; Fred Funk; Jim Furyk, Sergio Garcia, Bill Glasson, Bob
Goalby, Jay Haas, J.P. Hayes, Scott Hoch, John Huston, Trevor
Immelman (a), Lee Janzen, Brandt Jobe, Per-Ulrik Johansson, Steve
Jones, Hermamn Kaiser, Matt Kuchar (a), Hank Kuehne (a), Bernhard
Langer, Tom Lehman, Justin Leonard, Frank Lickliter, Davis Love
III, Sandy Lyle, Andrew Magee, Jeff Maggert, Shigeki Maruyama,
Billy Mayfair, Scott McCarron, Tom McKnight (a), Phil Mickelson;
John Miller (a); Larry Mize; Colin Montgomerie; Byron Nelson, Jack
Nicklaus; Greg Norman, Mark O'Meara, Jose Maria Olazabal, Jumbo
Ozaki, Arnold Palmer, Jesper Parnevik, Steve Pate, Corey Pavin,
Chris Perry, Gary Player, Nick Price, Loren Roberts, Gene Sarazen,
Vijay Singh, Jeff Sluman, Sam Snead, Craig Stadler, Payne Stewart,
Steve Stricker, Hal Sutton, David Toms, Bob Tway, Scott Verplank,
Art Wall Jr, Tom Watson, Brian Watts, Lee Westwood, Willie Wood,
Tiger Woods, Ian Woosnam, Fuzzy Zoeller.
</P>
<P>
   Glenn Sheeley writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
