<SLUG> BC-GOP-CORRECTION-0124-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX WASHINGTON BUREAU CORRECTION
 &HT;    By RICK CHRISTIE 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ In a story that moved Fri., Jan. 22, for
publication Sat., Jan. 23, the Cox News Service incorrectly
reported that Repubican National Committee Chairman Jim Nicholson
announced that the GOP's top priorities would not include the
banning of abortions.
</P>
<P>
   The story should have said that Nicholson, in announcing the
party's top priorities through the 2000 election, did not include
the banning of abortions.
</P>
<P>
   The Cox News Service regrets the error.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
