A5731 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HKN-NHLWEST24-COX     01-23 0613
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-NHLWEST24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Western Conference notes: The first domino
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Now that Vancouver general manager Brian Burke has traded Pavel
Bure, don't be surprised if coach Mike Keenan is the next big name
to be shipped out. Burke had said he would not hold Keenan
``exclusively responsible'' for the Canucks' problems as long as
Bure was holding out. It wouldn't seem that Burke gave Keenan much
of a short-term boost with the package from Florida. Only
defenseman Ed Jovanovski will provide immediate help. Dave Gagner
is too old (34), Mike Brown is too young (19) and goalie Kevin
Weekes is unsigned. But Burke already is turning up the pressure on
Keenan. ``I do think this is a playoff team,'' he said. ``I think
healthy we're a playoff team without the trade, and I think with
the trade we're clearly a playoff team.'' The Canucks beat Dallas
5-3 the day after the trade but then lost to Nashville 4-1. ``The
Nashville game was not a little bit of a disappointment,'' Burke
said. ``It was a total disappointment. Based on the first game
after the trade, we should have been able to ride this out a little
bit. But based on (the Nashville game), I have no comfort in
that.''
</P>
<P>
   Hamlet of Hollywood
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles coach Larry Robinson, who earlier this season
rejected a contract extension, now is questioning his abilities as
a coach after seeing his team lose three in a row after a brief
turnaround. ``I often question whether I'm a good coach _ a good
head coach. There are certain qualities to being a great head
coach. There are a lot of things I think about, and I don't know if
I communicate them properly.'' As to how he feels he needs to
improve, Robinson said, ``Reading people's personalities, being
able to take a guy aside and tell him exactly how I feel and maybe
the things he should be doing. My problem is maybe I care too much
about hurting a guy's feelings or telling a guy really what he's
playing like or what he should be doing. I try to put myself in the
same situation and how I'd like to be treated. Maybe one of the
qualities of being a great coach is being (a jerk). There are quite
a few of them around. . . . (Detroit's) Scotty Bowman is probably
the greatest coach of all time, and (former Montreal Canadiens
coach) Toe Blake was great, too. But I've heard stories about them
that would make your hair stand up. I can't treat people like
that.''
</P>
<P>
   Etc.
</P>
<P>
   Burke on Bure's old No. 10 jersey: ``The first player to ask for
it can have it.'' . . . Burke on comments by New York general
manager Mike Smith that he ``deserved a phone call'' from Burke to
tell him that a deal with Florida, and not the Rangers, was
imminent: ``He can whine all he wants.'' . . . Edmonton is
considering shipping Andre Kovalenko to Philadelphia for Alexander
Daigle. . . . Detroit is an astoundingly low 8-for-84 (9.5 percent)
on the power play in the last 17 games. . . . The Red Wings'
Brendan Shanahan has gone 14 games without a goal. . . .
Nashville's biggest problem in its expansion season is that it has
had to play games against Eastern Conference teams. The Predators
are 2-11-2 vs. the East and 14-14-2 against the West. . . . Dallas
is 2-4-1 in its last seven after starting the year 25-5-6, leaving
coach Ken Hitchcock concerned despite the best record at the
All-Star break. ``From the overall perspective, you want to be in
first place. But from where our game is right now, I think we've
got a lot of room to improve.''
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Schultz writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
