AMWEST _ With new planes on order, big expansion plans and a
sparkling headquarters building going up in downtown Tempe, America
West Airlines doesn't seem like a company with a giant ``For Sale''
sign on the door. But the carrier found itself in the center of
merger mania last week, with United Airlines publicly expressing
interest in a buyout and other big airlines saying they might take
a look. By DAWN GILBERTSON. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
