had lost his leadership position and was no longer eligible for the
extra money. On some days, even when the Legislature was not in
session, a family member pushed the ailing Aldridge's wheelchair
into the House, where he signed for his $60 in per diem pay, then
went home, House sources say. Through a ``special dispensation''
from House Speaker Jeff Groscost, Aldridge was able to collect more
money than any other member of the House. By CHRIS MOESER. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
