<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-MCGINNIS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MCGINNIS IS `BACK FOR GOOD'  
 TURNS DOWN BEARS, RETURNS TO CARDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Cardinals defensive coordinator Dave McGinnis told
friends in the Valley he wouldn't take the Chicago Bears' head
coaching job unless it was a good fit.
</P>
<P>
   He returned to Phoenix Saturday night, saddened that his past
two days in Chicago had turned into ``Groundhog Day,'' but anxious
to return to work with the Cardinals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told our players and this organization that if it wasn't
right, I wasn't leaving Arizona,'' McGinnis said after arriving at
Sky Harbor Airport with his wife, Kim. ``Now, I'm back in Arizona,
and I'm back for good.
</P>
<P>
   ``I love it here. The organization has been good to me. It's a
win-win situation for me.''
</P>
<P>
   McGinnis withdrew his name from consideration at the Bears
Saturday afternoon, 24 hours after the team called a news
conference to announce his hiring. He hadn't even accepted the job
at the time.
</P>
<P>
   The Bears wasted little time in naming a coach after McGinnis
pulled out. They hired Jacksonville defensive coordinator Dick
Jauron.
</P>
<P>
   `My emotions are sad because it turned out like this and
probably didn't have to,'' McGinnis said. ``Obviously, we all
thought it would turn out very good, and it wound up very sad.''
</P>
<P>
   McGinnis met with Bears officials for nearly four hours Saturday
morning to try to patch up their differences. But much of the
damage already had been done when the Bears announced the hiring
even though the two sides hadn't agreed on a contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought it could be worked out,'' McGinnis said. ``But I was
shocked at the way it happened. It was very awkward.
</P>
<P>
   ``Still, it wasn't like I was extremely wronged. Don't look at
me as a victim.''
</P>
<P>
   Bears President Michael McCaskey called Friday's premature
announcement of the hiring an ``internal foul up.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We made a mistake on that,'' McCaskey said. ``We didn't intend
for it to happen.''
</P>
<P>
   The Bears first offer to McGinnis was a four-year deal worth
$3.3 million in which only the first two years were guaranteed. On
Saturday, they increased the offer to a five-year deal, but there
was a buy-out after the third year.
</P>
<P>
   ``So after the second year, he would have felt as if he was on
the last year of his contract,'' a source close to McGinnis said.
``That's ridiculous.''
</P>
<P>
   McCaskey said the disagreement between the two sides had nothing
to do with money, the length of the contract or the structure of
the contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't care to go into it now and probably never will,''
McCaskey said. ``It's between me and Dave. These things happen.
Sometimes, they are a pathway to consideration of other things and
that's what happened in this case.''
</P>
<P>
   One thing that upset McGinnis is that he lost the services of
three assistants he hoped to hire during the confusion on Friday.
Leslie Frazier and Ron Rivera took positions as secondary coach and
linebacker coach, respectively at Philadelphia. Mike Martz, the St.
Louis Rams quarterback coach, was promoted to the Rams' offensive
coordinator instead of taking the same position with the Bears.
</P>
<P>
   Bears Vice President Mark Hatley, who conducted the first
interview with McGinnis 10 days ago in the Valley, said that if
McGinnis ``really wanted the job, he would have taken it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hat(ley) is outstanding, but he's an emotional guy,'' McGinnis
said. ``He wanted me to take the job.''
</P>
<P>
   McCaskey acknowledged that the McGinnis affair has been a
public-relations black eye for the Bears.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have some repair work to do,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   McGinnis said hoped to talk to Cardinals Coach Vince Tobin on
Saturday night. But he has been assured he will get his job back.
</P>
<P>
   ``I talked to Kathy (Tobin),'' McGinnis said of the head coach's
wife. ``I told her we were coming back if there wasn't anyone in my
office.
</P>
<P>
   '`Now, all I'm going to worry about is making the opponents
(next season) punt.''
</P>
<P>
   McCaskey got in touch with the remaining three candidates _
Buffalo offensive coordinator Joe Pendry, Green Bay offensive
coordinator Sherm Lewis and Jauron _ to fill the post of the fired
Dave Wannstedt.
</P>
<P>
   The hiring of Jauron means the Jaguars have lost both of their
coordinators. Offensive coordinator Chris Palmer was hired last
week as the first coach of the new Cleveland Browns.
</P>
<P>
   Bears spokesman Bryan Harlan said Jauron would be introduced as
the new coach at a news conference today. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-23-99 2355EST &QL; 
